Technical Report

Title: ex. A Mobile Application for Scheduling and Confirming Animal Feedings at a Metropolitan Zoo

Authors: Juliana, Khaleel, Andrew, Sulim

Faculty Advisor: 	Rich Hildred

Keywords: Mobile application, HTML 5, JavaScript

Abstract:
Ex., A need was perceived by the mangers at the Kitchener zoo to schedule feedings for the animals according to specified zoo personnel as animals sometimes went hungry with unfortunate results. The chief zookeeper and attendants were interviewed and requirements were gathered according to best industry practices. It was decided to create a desktop web application using ASP.NET as the client has appropriate licensing, and a partner mobile application using HTML 5 as this would result in maximum flexibility across devices and platforms. The system has been implemented and the client is now using it. There is potential for commercializing the application. 

Academic Purpose:
Ex. This project is intended to fulfill the requirements of the Systems Development: System Project course (INFO3800) in the Computer Programmer Analyst program at Conestoga College ITAL. 

Business/Technological Purpose:
Ex., This system will allow zoo managers to create schedules for zoo personnel to feed animals.  Personnel carrying handheld devices will use a mobile application to confirm the feedings have taken place or to flag them for rescheduling. (You might wish to include a screenshot here to give a stronger idea of how the system is used.) 

Our Contribution:
This section should include the main strengths from your Project Strengths document. Include the techniques, technologies and business features that best distinguish your project.  Include any innovative technical development and any innovative business features. A strength could always be that your project is a highly cost-effective solution for your client.

