Approach:
Document the methods used for gathering user requirements. Explain the choice the choice of methodologies and technologies. 

Discussion:
Did the completed project meet your expectations and those of the clients? What challenges did you have to overcome in implementing the project? Discuss any interesting fixes you made. Were there unexpected benefits?

Future Work:
If you were to continue with this work in the future, what features would you add? What corrections or adjustments you would make? (You don’t have to give away any ideas that you wish to commercialize.) Would it make sense for other CP or CPA groups to continue this work for the client?

Conclusions/Summary:
List three or four of the strongest ideas from this document, especially the ones you want to leave with the reader.
